  "doc_id": "54532",
  "text": "Ultrasonic online cleaning methods can effectively control membrane fouling [CITATION_1] . Ultrasonic waves have very special properties. The \"cavitation\" caused by the instantaneous release of ultrasonic energy concentrates on the solid-liquid interface, thus exerting a strong impact on the point of action and its surroundings and on the gel layer attached to the surface of the membrane. The precipitate produces a strong peeling effect [CITATION_2] . However, excessive ultrasonic strength and time of action will break up the sludge flocs, affecting sludge activity and damaging the membrane module [CITATION_3] . Therefore, the selection of appropriate ultrasonic intensity and time of action is essential for effective control of membrane fouling. Too long stoppage will affect the amount of water produced, too short to achieve the desired results",
